# Network Security Scanner

## 📌 Project Overview
The Network Security Scanner is a cybersecurity project developed to identify active devices, open ports, running services, and operating system details within a network. It helps security professionals discover vulnerabilities and improve overall network security using ethical scanning techniques.

## 🎯 Objectives
- Scan live hosts on a network
- Identify open TCP/UDP ports
- Detect running services
- Perform OS detection
- Improve network security

## ✨ Features
- Host Discovery
- Port Scanning
- Service Detection
- OS Detection
- Network Enumeration
- Security Assessment

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies
- Nmap
- Kali Linux
- Linux Terminal
- TCP/IP
- Networking Fundamentals

## 🚀 How to Run

```bash
nmap 192.168.1.1
nmap -A 192.168.1.1
nmap -p 22,80,443 192.168.1.1
nmap 192.168.1.0/24
```

